As one of the most prominent players in the industry with a presence in strategic locations around the world, Singapore-based Musim Mas is fully integrated across the entire spectrum of the palm oil supply chain. Search, sample, and chat with experts from our commercial team at Inter-Continental Oils and Fats (ICOF), a member of Musim Mas Group, on Knowde today.

data.name: INTERPALM
data.description: Interpalm is refined hard fractionated of palm oil.

data.name: MASEMUL
data.description: MASEMUL® emulsifiers are a range of products that are used in a variety of food applications ranging from bakery, confectionery, margarine, frozen desserts and dairy. Emulsifiers perform various functions such as the emulsification of two or more immiscible phases, starch complexing and dough strengthening in bread-making, demulsification in ice-cream, and as a drying agent for yeast. They are used in the following applications.

data.name: MASCEROL
data.description: Inter-Continental Oils & Fats (ICOF), a member of Musim Mas Group, serves vegetable refined Glycerine of various grades and feed-stocks backed by our Asian oleochemical production facilities as well as our European refinery Dutch Glycerin Refinery B.V. (DGR) located within Delfzijl Chemical Park providing easy logistical access to major European, Middle East, African and American end markets via road, rail, barge and sea. The material can be packed in drums or IBC as per request.

data.name: MASCOL
data.description: Used in the production of high-quality products, the applications of Fatty Alcohols range from detergents, surfactants, cosmetics, and industrial solvents.Naturally derived from Palm Oil and Palm Kernel Oil, we offer fatty alcohols with chain lengths ranging from C8 to C18.Short Chain Alcohols – C8, C810, C10Mid Cut Alcohols – C12, C1214, C1216, C1218, C14Long Chain Alcohols – C16, C1618 (30:70, 50:50, 70:30), C18We offer the Mid Cut Alcohols ex-tank in Europe and the US and thus have the capability to meet global supply chain requirements. For the long-chain alcohols, we also provide the product in pastilles form. Fatty Alcohol trademark, MASCOL™, meets all the stringent specification requirements across various industries.Fatty Alcohols and their derivatives find application in various home and personal care applications like creams and lotions, detergents, shampoos, and toothpastes. In addition, they are very widely used in agriculture, crude oil exploration, emulsion polymerization, paints and coatings, perfumery chemicals, pharmaceuticals, pulp and paper, lubricants, and in the preparation of textile auxiliaries.

data.name: MASCID
data.description: MASCID® products are Fatty Acid derivatives widely used in the Home and Personal Care industries. They can also be used as a raw material or as an intermediate for pharmaceutical, rubber, plastic, paint and lubricant industries. They are an effective high-quality substitute for many petroleum-based products.

data.name: MASESTER
data.description: Produced at the highest quality, our Esters serve as versatile ingredients in your formulations. The product range includes emollients, skin conditioners, emulsifiers, stabilizer, opacifiers and viscosity modifiers.Our MASESTER™ Medium Chain Triglycerides are, next to it's use in personal care, great ingredients for flavor, food & beverage and pharmaceutical industry. The versatile oil with helath benefits functions as solubilizer, clouding agent, excipient and wetting agent.MASESTER™ Functional Products are: PHO-free (Partially Hydrogenated Oil), non-GMO and nonallergenic derived from sustainable palm oil grown within Musim Mas plantations.All products are HALAL and KOSHER certified.

data.name: MASCOLETH
data.description: MASCOLETH® products are linear or branched alcohol ethoxylates that act as nonionic surfactants. They are intermediates for sulfation process, wetting agents, dispersants, emulsifier, foaming agents and also solubilizing agents.

data.name: MASPHATE
data.description:
MASPHATE® products are anionic surfactants, based on natural fatty alcohol and natural fatty alcohol ethoxylates.

Our anionic MASPHATE® range is widely used as emulsifier, emollients, foaming and wetting agents.

data.name: Vitrenol
data.description: Vitrenol® brand is a natural source of Tocotrienol-rich fraction Vitamin E, extracted from palm oil through a unique solvent-free extraction technology. This ensures our products are 100% natural and chemical-free. Vitamin E extracted from palm oil comprises Tocotrienols and Tocopherols, which exist as a natural complex at a ratio of 3:1. Vitrenol® may be used as a health and dietary supplement, in functional food and drinks and antiaging beauty creams. It is available in both liquid and powder forms at various concentrations to suit customers’ specific needs and applications.

data.name: MASEMUL® EB 1011
data.description: MASEMUL® EB 1011 is an emulsified vegetable fat designed to enhance bakery creations. As a bakery improver, MASEMUL® EB 1011 is crucial in maintaining softness, boosting bread volume, and ensuring excellent anti-staling properties. Experience its remarkable attributes, from imparting good dough extensibility to elevating your baked goods' quality.

data.name: MASPHATE® SLS 94 N
data.description: MASPHATE® SLS 94 N is produced from natural fatty alcohols. These highly concentrated dry surfactants offer formulators efficient and low carbon alternatives to traditional liquid surfactants. Given their excellent foaming property, Masphate® Sodium Lauryl Sulfate (SLS) is often used in various personal and home products such as toothpaste, hand soaps, body wash, detergents, and dishwashing liquids. It is also commonly used in industrial applications including emulsion polymerization and gypsum board manufacturing, and in agricultural formulations as a wetting agent. Free of 1,4 dioxane; Masphate® SLS provides formulators with a valued ingredient option in their pursuit of regulatory-compliant, efficient, and effective cleaning formulations. Masphate® SLS is offered in three product forms including needles, granules, and powder.

data.name: MASCOL® 18/98P

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 1-Hydroxyoctadecane, 1-Octadecanol, Alcohol Stearylicus, Alfol 18, Atalco S, Octadecan-1-ol, Octadecanol, Octadecanol NF, Octadecyl Alcohol, Stearal, Stearic Alcohol, Stearol

data.description:
MASCOL® 18/98P is a versatile ingredient serving as a viscosity modifier, emulsifier, emollient, film former, and re-fatting agent. It brings an array of benefits, including:


	Emulsion Stabilization
	Hydration
	Irritation Reduction
	Moist Feel
	Moisturizing
	Non-drying Effects
	Skin Protection
	Smoothing
	Softening
	Water Absorbency


MASCOL® 18/98P applications extend to the realm of personal care, where it enhances various products.

data.name: MASCOL® 16/98P

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 1-Cetanol, 1-Hexadecyl Alcohol, 1-Hydroxyhexadecane, Cetanol, Cetostearyl Alcohol, Cetylic Alcohol, Ethal, Ethol, Hexadecyl Alcohol, Palmityl Alcohol, N-Hexadecan-1-ol

data.description: MASCOL® 16/98P is a high-quality, naturally derived fatty alcohol. It can be used as an emollient, emulsifier, stabilizer, thickening agent, or foam inhibitor in various applications like creams and lotions, shampoos, or detergents to moisturize and smooth the skin and hair, as well as to reduce irritations. MASCOL® 16/98P is vegan, non-GMO, non-allergenic, and derived from sustainable palm oil, produced by the Musim Mas group. The product is offered as a liquid or in white solid form as pastilles.

data.name: MASCID® 1012
data.description: MASCID® 1012 is derived from Sustainable Palm Oil and endorsed by COSMOS. This vegan, non-gmo, and non-allergenic ingredient excels as an emulsifier, stabilizer, and surfactant in solid and liquid soaps, body washes, and various rinse-off applications. Elevate your cleansing ritual with the innovative power of MASCID® 1012.

data.name: MASESTER® E7000
data.description: MASESTER® E7000 is a versatile, palm-based ingredient derived from fractionated fatty acids (mainly caprylic and capric acids) and refined glycerine. This odorless product finds applications across the flavor, food, and beverage sectors, as well as the pharmaceutical industry. Serving as a solubilizer, clouding agent, excipient, and wetting agent, MASESTER® E7000 seamlessly enhances formulations.

data.name: MASCID® 1318
data.description: MASCID® 1318 is composed of oleic acid and is recommended for use in the manufacturing of soap and detergents as well as an emulsifier, solubilizer, and stabilizer for food ingredients and pharmaceuticals. It can also be utilized as an emulsifier for metalworking fluids, resins, and surface coatings, an emollient or superfatting agent for cosmetics, and as an adhesive.

data.name: MASCOL® 68/50P
data.description: MASCOL® 68/50P is a high-quality blend of natural cetyl and stearyl alcohol (50:50). It can be used as an emollient, emulsifier, stabilizer, refatting agent, or opacifier in various applications like creams and lotions, shampoos, or detergents to moisturize and smooth the skin and hair, as well as to reduce irritation. MASCOL® 68/50P is vegan, non-GMO, non-allergenic, and derived from sustainable palm oil, produced by the Musim Mas group. The product comes as a liquid or in white solid form as pastilles. Please refer to MASCOL® 68/50P for a 30:70 mix of Cetyl Stearyl Alcohol. Our MASCOL product range is halal and kosher.

data.name: MASCID® 1802
data.description: MASCID® 1802 stearic acid is derived from sustainable palm oil and is COSMOS-approved, vegan, non-GMO, and non-allergenic. Applications include emollients, emulsifiers, stabilizers, and conditioners (in creams, lotions, shampoos, and body washes). With excellent refatting, smoothing, and anti-irritating properties, it makes perfect applications in skin, sun, hair, and lip care. Other applications include a rheology modifier for high-quality formulation creations.

As a bakery improver, MASEMUL® EB 1011 is crucial in maintaining softness, boosting bread volume, and ensuring excellent anti-staling properties. Experience its remarkable attributes, from imparting good dough extensibility to elevating your baked goods' quality.

data.name: MASEMUL® DMG 9502H
data.description: MASEMUL® DMG 9502H is a key player in the creation of margarine and bakery products. Its role as an emulsifier contributes to the quality and performance of these food items. Within the markets of food and nutrition, printing, and packaging, MASEMUL® DMG 9502H finds its significance, enhancing both the culinary and packaging aspects of your products.

data.name: MASEMUL® EC 5001
data.description: MASEMUL® EC 5001 is a triumph in thwarting oil separation within fat-based spreads. Embrace its unwavering stability, uniform texture, and exceptional spreadability. Bask in the luxurious high surface gloss it imparts, with the added delight of no large crystals forming on the surface. MASEMUL® EC 5001 is ideal in food and nutrition, shining in confectionery and convenience food applications.

data.name: MASEMUL® EF 2001
data.description: MASEMUL® EF 2001 is a baking essential integrated into cake recipes, enhancing batter handling and overall cake quality. Witness improved softness and prolonged moisture retention throughout the product's shelf life. Combined with shortening, it enhances the creaming process of high-ratio cakes, promising exceptional culinary outcomes.

data.name: MASEMUL® EF 2002
data.description: MASEMUL® EF 2002 is a batter conditioner and emulsifier. It ensures a robust and high-performing cake gel. It improves batter handling and overall cake quality. It significantly improves softness and moisture retention. MASEMUL® EF 2002 can be used for sponges, muffins, cupcakes, Swiss rolls, and butter or cream cakes.

data.name: MASEMUL® EF 25
data.description: MASEMUL® EF 25 is a batter conditioner and emulsifier seamlessly integrated into cake recipes, enhancing batter handling and overall cake quality. It improves softness and moisture retention throughout the product's shelf life. When combined with shortening, it enhances the creaming process of high-ratio cakes, promising exceptional culinary outcomes.

data.name: MASEMUL® EM 3001
data.description: MASEMUL® EM 3001 is an industrial margarine renowned in bakery and confectionery applications. It serves as a vital fat source, contributing structure and delightful taste attributes to products. MASEMUL® EM 3001 is a versatile cake and cream margarine tailored for pound cakes, fat-based bakery fillings, toppings, and short-crust pastries, ensuring exceptional results in every creation.

data.name: MASEMUL® EM 3002
data.description: MASEMUL® EM 3002 is a versatile, vegetable oil-based margarine designed for a wide array of applications, from spreading and shallow frying to baking. Emulsifier blends like MASEMUL® EM 3002 enhance emulsion stability and margarine performance, ensuring exceptional culinary results across the board.

data.name: MASEMUL® MDG 4502
data.description: MASEMUL® MDG 4502 is a vital component enhancing chewing gum bases and candies. Functions include: Emulsification, anti-sticking, and extrusion aid. Operating within the agriculture and feed, food and nutrition, and printing and packaging markets, MASEMUL® MDG 4502 contributes to diverse industries.

data.name: MASEMUL® PGE 4060
data.description: MASEMUL® PGE 4060 is a liquid-state, proficient polyglycerol ester derived from the fusion of refined vegetable oil and polyglycerol. MASEMUL® PGE 4060 is used as an emulsifier, batter conditioner, and whipping agent in various food applications. From bakery and confectionery to convenience foods, cooking oils and fat products, dairy, desserts, and fruit preparations.

data.name: MASEMUL® PGE 5702
data.description: MASEMUL® PGE 5702 is a polyglycerol ester meticulously crafted by combining refined vegetable fatty acids with polyglycerol. Presenting itself in solid bead form, it takes center stage in the world of food and nutrition, particularly bakery, confectionery, desserts, and fruit preparations. Experience its transformative features, including amplified volume, enhanced softness, optimized cell structure, and prolonged shelf life—all tailored to elevate medium- or high-fat cakes.

data.name: MASEMUL® PGMS 9502
data.description: MASEMUL® PGMS 9502 is a versatile ingredient with a significant role in cake mixes, ice cream, and whipping creams. It serves as both an Emulsifier and Whipping Agent, enhancing the texture and quality of various food products. Available in both beads and solid forms, MASEMUL® PGMS 9502 finds its applications across Bakery, Cooking oils and Fat products, and Savory and Culinary realms within the Food and Nutrition sector.

data.name: MASEMUL® PGPR 9090
data.description: MASEMUL® PGPR 9090 is a potent polyglycerol polyricinoleate emulsifier created with refined castor oil fatty acids and polyglycerol. Found in liquid form, its impact resonates across the spectrum of food and nutrition. From confectionery, convenience foods, desserts, and fruit preparations to compound chocolate and ice cream coatings, it offers unparalleled benefits.

data.name: MASEMUL® SMS 5502
data.description: MASEMUL® SMS 5502 is a potent emulsifier - sorbitan monostearate, made through the fusion of refined vegetable fatty acids and sorbitol. Available as both beads and solids, MASEMUL® SMS 5502 has food and nutrition applications ranging from bakery endeavors to diverse culinary creations.

data.name: MASEMUL® SSL 2802
data.description: MASEMUL® SSL 2802 has applications including emulsification, dough conditioning, and dough strengthening. Presented in solid bead form, MASEMUL® SSL 2802 is used in many applications, including animal health and nutrition in agriculture, and beverages in food and nutrition.

data.name: MASEMUL® SSL 3302
data.description: MASEMUL® SSL 3302 is crafted through the fusion of refined fatty acids with lactic acid; its prowess spans multiple functions: Emulsification, clouding, dough conditioning, dough strengthening, and whipping. MASEMUL® SSL 3302 has applications in animal health and nutrition, agriculture and feed, beverage, and food and nutrition

data.name: MASEMUL® STS 2002
data.description: MASEMUL® STS 2002 is a sorbitan tristearate created from the fusion of refined vegetable fatty acids and sorbitol. It is an excellent Anti-Blooming Agent and Emulsifier. It seamlessly integrates into fats, compound coatings, and fillings, enhancing their properties. MASEMUL® STS 2002 has application in beverage and food applications.

data.name: MASEMUL® STS 5002
data.description: MASEMUL® STS 5002 sorbitan tristearate is created by fusing refined vegetable fatty acids with sorbitol. As both an anti-crystallizing agent and an emulsifier, it excels at maintaining product integrity. Available in beads and solid forms, MASEMUL® STS 5002 finds its aptitude within cooking oils and fat products. Explore its prowess in enhancing culinary experiences within the food and nutrition sector, ensuring the highest quality in your creations.

data.name: MASEMUL® MDG 6002
data.description: MASEMUL® MDG 6002 is a specialized ingredient, vital for ice cream perfection. Serving as an emulsifier, it contributes to the smooth texture and consistent quality of ice cream. Available in both bead and solid forms, MASEMUL® MDG 6002 finds its applications in a wide range of food and nutrition domains, including bakery, confectionery, cooking oils and fat products, dairy, desserts, and fruit preparations, as well as savory and culinary creations.

data.name: MASEMUL® AMG 9002
data.description:
MASEMUL® AMG 9002 is an acetic acid ester of monoglycerides derived from fully hydrogenated palm-based oil. It is an emulsifier with a number of food and nutrition appliciations including:


	Bakery and confectionery
	Cooking oils
	Fat products
	Dairy
	desserts
	Fruit preparations
	Savory and culinary creations

data.name: MASEMUL® DMG 9320-NH
data.description: MASEMUL® DMG 9320-NH is a distilled monoglyceride derived from refined palm-based oil. FUnctions include fats and oils, fatty acids and lipids, and emulsification. MASEMUL® DMG 9320-NH has food and nutrition applications that include beverages, food, and nutrition and well-being.

data.name: MASEMUL® EC 5002
data.description: MASEMUL® EC 5002 is a remarkable offering. Its role is centered around fatty acids and lipids, and it proudly bears the labeling claims of being Non-GMO, trans-fat-free, and naturally derived. in the realm of food and nutrition, MASEMUL® EC 5002 finds its applications in bakery, confectionery, cooking oils and fat products, dairy, desserts, and fruit preparations, as well as in savory and culinary creations.

data.name: MASEMUL® EC 5101
data.description: MASEMUL® EC 5101 is an integrated blend of fat and emulsifiers. It is used for baking stable-fat fillings in cookies. This product improves the bake-stable performance of cocoa and white-based fillings and maintains the smooth, creamy texture of the filling.

data.name: MASEMUL® EC 5401
data.description: MASEMUL® EC 5401 is a blend of triglycerides based on fully hydrogenated vegetable oil and mono (E471). This product is suitable for fat-based confectionery fillings, including shortening for wafer fillings and biscuit creams. MASEMUL® EC 5401 is an integrated blend of fat and emulsifier to improve crystallization for fat-based fillings.

data.name: MASEMUL® EF 2003
data.description: MASEMUL® EF 2003 is a premium emulsifier blend crafted for producing exceptional α-cake gel. This easy-handling pellet emulsifier ensures unparalleled stability and production reliability. Embrace the seamless performance of MASEMUL® EF 2003, a vital asset in the realm of food and nutrition applications.

data.name: MASEMUL® EF 2004
data.description: MASEMUL® EF 2004 is an emulsifier blend. It provides good stability and improves cake batter quality. MASEMUL® EF 2004 is also used for producing standard α-cake gel and is ideal for use within the vertical mixer production of all types of cake.

data.name: MASEMUL® EF 2005
data.description: MASEMUL® EF 2005 is a specialized emulsifier blend designed for producing α-cake gel, particularly in propylene glycol-free formulations. Crafted in easy-to-handle pellet form, this emulsifier ensures cake gels boast exceptional stability and whipping ability. A versatile solution for food and nutrition applications, especially for baking.

data.name: MASEMUL® OB 1015
data.description: MASEMUL® OB 1015 provides non-hydrogenated, trans-free, and non-GMO vegetable-based triglycerides. Functions include fatty acids and lipids, offering valuable attributes. In food and nutrition, MASEMUL® OB 1015 is used in bakery, confectionery, cooking oils and fat products, dairy, desserts, and fruit preparations.

data.name: MASEMUL® EB 1005
data.description: MASEMUL® EB 1005 emulsifier blend is a bread texture softener and dough strengthener. It offers a complete solution to bread manufacturers and doesn't require additional emulsifiers. MASEMUL® EB 1005 provides enhanced machinability, bread volume, shape retention, and extended shelf life.

data.name: MASEMUL® EB 1006
data.description: MASEMUL® EB 1006 is a specialized addition to bun and dough formulas, including baked, steamed, or fried. This product enhances handling and overal quality, increasing dough tolerance while delivering remarkable consistency. Also provides enhanced machinability, longer shelf life, and amplified bun volume.

data.name: MASEMUL® EB 1007
data.description: MASEMUL® EB 1007 improves dough handling in terms of machinability, volume, shelf life, and eating quality in frozen and fresh pizza dough formulas. MASEMUL® EB 1007 can also increase dough strength and improve texture and bite (short bite, crispness, and crunchy bite) in cookie recipes.

data.name: MASEMUL® EC 5102
data.description: MASEMUL® EC 5102 is a liquid functional blend that imparts a lusciously smooth and creamy texture to fillings post-baking. Tailored to improve keep premium goods bake-stable, MASEMUL® EC 5102 specializes in chocolate and white center fillings, ensuring your creations reach new heights of indulgence.

data.name: MASEMUL® EF 2006
data.description: MASEMUL® EF 2006 is a user-friendly food-grade emulsifier blend in convenient paste form, tailored for bakery premix manufacturers. This remarkable ingredient combines the benefits of various emulsifiers into one functional solution. Crafted from vegetable-based, non-GMO raw materials, MASEMUL® EF 2006 offers a seamless way to elevate your bakery creations.

data.name: MASEMUL® EM 3003
data.description: MASEMUL® EM 3003 is a margarine that is widely used in laminated products such as croissants, danish, and other puff pastries to improve lamination and expansion. The plasticity of puff pastry margarine plays a vital role in the lamination process in order to ensure unbroken, homogeneous, thin layers of puff pastry margarine in the dough. This provides structure and volume to the laminated products. MASEMUL® EM 3003 is an emulsifier blend in pastilles form for puff pastry margarine application.

data.name: MASEMUL® EM 3004
data.description: MASEMUL® EM 3004 is an emulsifier blend in paste form. It provides a stable emulsion for low-fat spread production. The low-fat spread contains a high proportion of water, emulsifiers, and stabilizers. It is intended for use in bread and other yeast goods applications to improve freshness, quality, and texture.

data.name: MASEMUL® DMG 9502
data.description: MASEMUL® DMG 9502 is a versatile ingredient used in margarine, bakery products, and coffee whiteners. It acts as an emulsifier and extrusion aid, contributing to the quality and performance of various food products. Applications include agriculture and feed, food and nutrition, printing, and packaging markets. MASEMUL® DMG 9502 brings its unique benefits to a wide array of industries.
